The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Pak duo appears at ICC hearing
                                                                                                                       7                                      Pak duo appears at ICC hearing
                      
	Dubai: The International Cricket Council (ICC) Saturday started the two-day hearing on the appeals by Pakistan players Salman Butt and Mohammed Aamer against the suspensions imposed on them for their alleged involvement in spot-fixing.         
	The first day of the hearing lasted for more than eight hours and will continue on Sunday.         
	The two cricketers were accompanied by their lawyers  Butt by Khalid R Anjha, a former law minister, and former Pakistan player Aftab Gul, while Aamer was with Shahid Karim.         
	Both Butt and Aamer appeared before ICCs code of conduct commissioner with hope that the suspensions would be removed.(PTI)                                                                                                                     
